-- Ex-Sony employees sue, claim company failed to protect data
-- By David Ingram
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 12:23PM EST
-- None



Dec 16 (Reuters) - Sony Pictures Entertainment Inc <6758.T><SNE.N> has been sued in a class action by two people who described themselves as former employees and accused the company of failing to protect employee data.

The lawsuit was filed on Monday in U.S. District Court for the Central District of California and alleged that Sony failed to secure its computer network and failed to stop hackers.